import numpy as np

def algorithm(train_samples, train_parity, test_samples):
    n = train_samples.shape[1]
    print(f"Shape of train_samples: {train_samples.shape}") # Debug line 1
    
    aug_matrix = np.hstack((train_samples, train_parity[:, np.newaxis]))
    print(f"Shape of augmented matrix: {aug_matrix.shape}") # Debug line 2
    
    for i in range(n):
        pivot_row = np.argmax(aug_matrix[i:, i]) + i
        print(f"Pivot row for i={i}: {pivot_row}") # Debug line 3
        
        if aug_matrix[pivot_row, i] != 0:
            if pivot_row != i:
                aug_matrix[[i, pivot_row]] = aug_matrix[[pivot_row, i]]
            aug_matrix[i+1:][(aug_matrix[i+1:, i] == 1)] = (aug_matrix[i+1:][(aug_matrix[i+1:, i] == 1)] - aug_matrix[i]) % 2
        print(f"Augmented matrix after processing row {i}:\n{aug_matrix}") # Debug line 4
        
    true_bits = np.zeros(n, dtype=int)
    for i in reversed(range(n)):
        true_bits[i] = aug_matrix[i, n] - np.sum(aug_matrix[i, i+1:n] * true_bits[i+1:])
        print(f"True bits after processing row {i}: {true_bits}") # Debug line 5
    
    test_parity = (np.sum(test_samples, axis=1) + true_bits.sum()) % 2
    print(f"Final test_parity: {test_parity}") # Debug line 6
    
    return test_parity
